The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Airlines mull fare hike

 New Delhi, Aug. 2: Domestic airlines are thinking of raising fares by Rs 100-150 in the wake of a 3-3.5 per cent increase in jet fuel prices from today.

 Top officials said most airlines were mulling a fuel surcharge hike. Indian and SpiceJet officials said they would hold meetings to review fuel costs and announce the surcharge over the weekend. 

 Jet fuel costs account for 40 per cent of an airlines operating costs.




